verbose_text: The lower expression levels of elastase, trypsin, amylase, and carboxypeptidase, etc. (ela3l, try, amy2a, cpa1) genes suggest that the downstream effects of snapc3, lsm8, and tnpo3 mutations converge on malfunction of the exocrine pancreas (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
evidence: levels of elastase, trypsin, amylase, and carboxypeptidase
